definitions.definition: A flat piece of coarse material used for wiping one’s feet, or as a decorative or protective floor covering.
examples: Wipe your feet on the mat before coming in.

definitions.definition: A small flat piece of material used to protect a surface from anything hot or rough; a coaster .
examples: They put mats on the table during mealtimes.

definitions.definition: ( athletics ) A floor pad to protect athletes.
examples: The high jumper cleared the bar and landed safely on the mat .

definitions.definition: A thin layer of woven , non-woven, or knitted fiber that serves as reinforcement to a material.
A thin surface layer; superficial cover.
examples: Iceland moss growing in a mat

definitions.definition: ( video games slang , chiefly in the plural ) Clipping of material .
examples: I used up all my mats cranking 90s and ended up getting one-pumped .

definitions.definition: ( coppersmithing ) An alloy of copper , tin , iron , etc.; white metal .
Alternative form of matte ( “ instrument for producing a dull, lustreless surface ” ) .
